com.example.cardiobook

Class BPs

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.cardiobook.BPs
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AddBP

    public abstract class BPs
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

    BPs is an abstract data type which holds all the information on a blood pressure entry. It implements serializable because if it can be serialized, it can be sent to various activities using intent.putExtra() and received using intent.getSerializableExtra() Acknowledgements: https://www.techjini.com/blog/passing-objects-via-intent-in-android/

    See Also:
    Serializable, Serialized Form

      • BPs

        public BPs(java.lang.String day,
           java.lang.String time,
           int systolic,
           int diastolic,
           int rate,
           int position)

        Method used to create a new BP entry. Calling this method will create a new BP with its comment blank.

        Parameters:
        day - date of the new BP to be entered
        time - time of the new BP to be entered
        systolic - systolic pressure of the new BP to be entered
        diastolic - diastolic pressure of the new BP to be entered
        rate - heart rate of the new BP to be entered
        position - position of the new BP to be entered
